    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing 17 species in one family found in oceans of the Southern Hemisphere having flipperlike wings for propulsion underwater; short stout webbed feet, upright stance upright, and short dense feathers that are molted in patches.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
